venues.name: O2 City Hall, Newcastle

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: If you're picking up tickets for a show that you're attending, please only come to the Box Office when the doors open on the day of the event.
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: The O2 City Hall Box Office is open for immediate pre-performance collections and sales on performance days from the advertised 'doors open' time until curtain up on the main act.

venues.parkingDetail: NCP operate a number of car parks close to the City Hall, and spaces for your visit can be pre-booked. John Dobson Street is open until 11.29pm and Carliol Square (which has pedestrian access onto Pilgrim Street) is open 24hrs. There are five parking spaces for blue badge holders in College Street Car Park, and a number of spaces a short distance away on John Dobson Street, close to NCP Car Park. Most parking meters in the local vicinity are free to blue badge holders.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: O2 City Hall Newcastle strive to make all our shows accessible to everyone and work with Attitude Is Everything and Nimbus Disability to make sure things keep improving. Venue also accepts the Access Card. It's not compulsory, but it means you won't have to provide repeat details every time you book, and lets venue know about any support or facilities you'll need when you visit. Wheelchair spaces These are available when you book, but they are limited on a first come, first served basis. Please get in touch with venue box office before you buy your tickets between 12pm and 4pm, Monday to Friday, on +44 (0)191 249 6050 or email boxoffice@o2cityhallnewcastle.co.uk to advise your access and personal assistant requirements. You can also contact venue through Next Generation Text Service by 18002 +44 (0)191 260 2020. Companion ticket If you need a ticket for a companion or personal assistant, please just let venue box office know when you book. Venue offers one companion ticket, free of charge, to provide support you need and additional assistance in the event of an emergency evacuation. Proof of eligibility will be required. Guide and hearing assistance dogs are welcome Additional Information: Wheelchair users O2 City Hall Newcastle has 6 seating areas available for every show for wheelchair users. It is necessary for wheelchair seating to be booked in advance, via the box office. Any customer booking a wheelchair seat will receive comprehensive information on access to the City Hall and its facilities when booking. Access for wheelchair users is only possible via a side door on College Street. You should see a steward at the front doors who will arrange for this to be opened and a steward will direct you to your seats.

generalInfo.generalRule: No cameras, video cameras or audio recording. No food, bottles, cans or alcohol to be brought onto the premises. No smoking. Security measures are in place so there will be bag checks on arrival. Only one small bag per person is permitted, and it must not be bigger than A4 size. Height: 29.7cm Width: 21cm Depth: 15cm Large bags, including rucksacks, are not allowed and there are no facilities to leave any luggage so please make alternative arrangements. If you really have to bring a bag and its preferable you don't, please make sure its small.

ada.adaCustomCopy:
To better accommodate your needs, O2 City Hall Newcastle has requested that all Accessible Ticketing requests be solicited only through their representatives. Please contact a Newcastle City Hall representative for further help with your ticket purchase.*   Advance ticket purchase may be required.

* Box office information is subject to change.

There are 6 spaces in the stalls on which priority is given to wheelchair users, There is an accessible toilet in the ground floor foyer, There are two blue badge parking spaces on College Street and most parking meters are free to blue badge holders. Level access to the auditorium is via College Street. 

The balcony seating is accessible via steps only so not recommend for patrons with mobility issues
ada.adaHours: Box office closed unless day of event when we open a minimum of 1 hour before a performance. for any box office needs prior to event day please reach contact the O2 Academy Newcastle

events.name: Coldplace - the World's Leading Tribute To Coldplay
Coldplace -The World's Leading Tribute To Coldplay

ada.adaCustomCopy:
The venue does not sell separate tickets for their accessible viewing area or disabled access tickets, only general admission.  If you are a wheelchair user and wish to be seated in the venue's wheelchair viewing area, please first purchase a general admission ticket and then contact the venue and they can allocate you a space.  Please note this is first come, first served and spaces are limited and the venue would therefore advise contacting them as soon as possible to try and secure a space. Please also note you may be asked to provide proof of access requirements.  The venue cannot provide extra tickets for this area if the show is sold out.

Once tickets have been purchased please email The Leadmill via ticketing@leadmill.co.uk to arrange."

* Box office information is subject to change.

venues.name: Marvel Stadium

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Please check the Marvel Stadium website for Event Day Box Office Opening Hours.

venues.parkingDetail: You will find it easy to drive to Marvel Stadium. Major street extensions include Latrobe Street Station. There will be plenty of parking at Marvel Stadium. There is on-site parking available for 2500 cars. Some 4000 spaces can also be found in the areas next to Marvel Stadium. Back in the Western end of the CBD there are some 12,000 spaces, most of which are generally available for casual hire. The Stadium also provides 52 designated parking bays for the mobility impaired
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Nothing has been overlooked in the planning of Marvel Stadium, including care and consideration for patrons who are mobility impaired, whether you are in a wheelchair or use a walking aid. MOBILITY IMPAIRED SEATING There are a variety of seating options and price categories for mobility impaired patrons. There are wheelchair bays, and sections with seats for patrons who use a walking frame, cane or are injured. These seats have excellent views and there is no seat directly in front. The precise location of the mobility impaired seating will vary according to the type of event being held and also price type. For some events, certain seats are designed as being ambulatory-accesible. These are for use by the patrons who cannot negotiate stairs but do not require seating allocated for mobility impaired patrons. Seating for companions is available alongside the bay or seat allocated to mobility impaired patrons-subject to availabilty.

ada.adaPhones:
1300 883 622
 
or 

Email:

Email your Accessible Seating request to mail.bookings@ticketmaster.com.au. Please ensure you include the Event Name, Venue, Date and Time along with your contact details.
ada.adaCustomCopy: Please call Ticketmaster's dedicated Marvel Stadium Accessible Seating Line if you have Wheelchair, Companion Card or Special Needs booking requirements.
ada.adaHours: Service Hours: Monday - Saturday 9am - 8pm; Sunday 9am - 5pm AEST (closed Christmas / Boxing Day)

events.name: Coldplay - Music Of The Spheres World Tour
events.info: For Subpac and Touch Tour inquiries, please email access@coldplay.com. Tickets will be on a print delay until further notice.
events.pleaseNote: Fees & Charges for Primary Tickets: The following fees apply to primary tickets these are tickets sold on behalf of the event organiser sold online*: A payment processing fee of no more than 2.3% applies to purchases which includes administration and associated infrastructure costs. This will be added to the price displayed. A Handling Fee of $8.00 per transaction applies over the phone and $5.00 online. A delivery fee may apply depending on the mode of delivery selected. *Different fees may apply for sales by phone or at outlets or at the venue Box Office. An Eden Park Stadium Levy of $3.95 applies to each ticket. Fees & Charges for Resale Tickets: Resale Tickets may be available for this event. These are tickets sold by fans and are verified by Ticketmaster. A Resale Seller Fee of no more than 5% of the resale ticket price and a handling Fee of $8.00 per transaction apply to purchases of Resale Tickets.

ticketLimit.info: There is a ticket limit of 4 per customer during the Presale and a ticket limit of 6 during the Public Onsale.

venues.name: Eden Park

boxOfficeInfo.acceptedPaymentDetail: Cash, EFTPOS, Visa, MasterCard, American Express, Diners
boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Tickets can be collected from Gates A, D, E & H on game day however please note gate opening times may vary and some gates may not be open for all games.

venues.parkingDetail: On non-game days, Eden Park has over 300 car parks available. When a game is on at Eden park, temporary parking restrictions may apply to the Park itself and streets in the immediate area. Parking on Game Day: While there is no parking at Eden Park on a game day, we encourage the use of public transport for games at the Eden Park. Onsite Parking: Some areas around the stadium, including areas within the parking zone, are reserved for public transport and other traffic management uses. Residents' who are Parking Permit Holders are not able to park in these areas. These areas are marked on the residents' newsletter map which is delivered a few days before each game and will be clearly signposted on the event day. When a game is on, the Traffic Management Plans are put in place and enforced by Auckland Transport. If you have any questions regarding game day traffic management, parking or transport, please phone Auckland Transport on 09 355 3553. Alternatively check www.edenpark.co.nz for more information on Parking.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: Disabled patrons have free entry to the stadium and disabled seating facilities for selected matches including Super Rugby and ITM Cup Rugby. Care givers are also free (for Super Rugby and ITM Cup) and tickets can be obtained through Auckland Rugby Union on (09) 815 4823. There are a limited number of disabled parks available on Cricket Avenue, in the North Stand carpark (Entrance P1 and P2) and in the South Stand (Entrance P5) on a first come, first served basis.

generalInfo.generalRule: Important things you should know: • Eden Park is a smoke-free environment. Smoking is not permitted. • Intoxicated persons will not be allowed entry. • There is a liquor-ban in the surrounding neighbourhood during all events. • All patrons entering the Stadium do so at their own risk • All patrons entering the Stadium must occupy the seat that they have been allocated • Umbrellas may not be raised within the Stadium • There shall be no unsolicited selling of merchandise, advertising or promotional giveaways • Liquor will not be served to minors and intoxicated persons and no patron may remove liquor from the Stadium • Children under the age of 14 years must be supervised by an adult at all times Note: Failure to comply with a direction from Event Management Staff at Eden Park Stadium or Police to leave the Stadium may render the patron liable to arrest and prosecution for the offence of trespass under Section 4 of the Trespass Act 1980, as amended, which is punishable on conviction by a fine not exceeding $1,000 or a term of imprisonment not exceeding 3 months in terms of section 11 (a) of the Trespass Act 1980, as amended.

ada.adaCustomCopy: Please call the Ticketmaster Contact Centre if you require wheelchair or accessible seating bookings, or are otherwise unable to complete a ticket purchase online.
ada.adaHours: Monday to Sunday: 9am to 5pm (excludes Public Holidays)

There are a limited number of disabled parks available on Cricket Avenue, in the North Stand carpark (Entrance P1 and P2) and in the South Stand (Entrance P5) on a first come, first served basis.

generalInfo.generalRule: Important things you should know: • Eden Park is a smoke-free environment. Smoking is not permitted. • Intoxicated persons will not be allowed entry. • There is a liquor-ban in the surrounding neighbourhood during all events. • All patrons entering the Stadium do so at their own risk • All patrons entering the Stadium must occupy the seat that they have been allocated • Umbrellas may not be raised within the Stadium • There shall be no unsolicited selling of merchandise, advertising or promotional giveaways • Liquor will not be served to minors and intoxicated persons and no patron may remove liquor from the Stadium • Children under the age of 14 years must be supervised by an adult at all times Note: Failure to comply with a direction from Event Management Staff at Eden Park Stadium or Police to leave the Stadium may render the patron liable to arrest and prosecution for the offence of trespass under Section 4 of the Trespass Act 1980, as amended, which is punishable on conviction by a fine not exceeding $1,000 or a term of imprisonment not exceeding 3 months in terms of section 11 (a) of the Trespass Act 1980, as amended.

events.info: Join us for an unforgettable concert experience on the first Friday of 2024! Get ready to rock out as our bands pay tribute to the incredible Dave Matthews Band, the iconic John Cougar Mellencamp, the electrifying U2, and the mesmerizing Coldplay.Prepare to be captivated by their chart-topping hits, soulful melodies, and energetic performances that will have you singing along all night long. Get your tickets now for an evening filled with unforgettable memories and timeless tunes!
